All 3 passthrough commands have meaningful `args()` implementations that build from their struct fields:
- **clean**: `-p pkg`, `--release`
- **clippy**: `-p pkg`, `--workspace`
- **fmt**: `-p pkg`, `--all`, `--check`

So with the helper function approach, each would call:
```rust
fn execute(&self, project_root: &Path) -> Result<ExitCode> {
    run_cargo("clean", &self.build_args(), project_root)
}

fn build_args(&self) -> Vec<OsString> {
    // current args() logic
}
```

Or inline the args building. Either way, `args()` becomes a regular method (not trait method).
